============================================================
  QUESTION & ANSWER PAIRS
============================================================

Q1: What is gravity?
A1: Gravity is an attractive force between all masses.
     Newton described it as F = Gm1m2/r². Einstein refined
     it as spacetime curvature in general relativity.

Q2: What is capitalism?
A2: Capitalism is an economic system where private
     individuals own the means of production and markets
     determine prices and production through supply and
     demand.

Q3: What is the Renaissance?
A3: The Renaissance (14th-17th century) was a cultural
     rebirth in Europe featuring renewed interest in Greco-
     Roman art, humanism, and early science. Began in Italy;
     spread across Europe.

Q4: What is metabolism?
A4: Metabolism is all chemical reactions in an organism
     that maintain life: catabolism (breaking molecules for
     energy) and anabolism (building complex molecules from
     simple ones).

Q5: What is the internet?
A5: The internet is a global network of interconnected
     computers using TCP/IP protocols. It began as ARPANET
     in 1969 and became public with the World Wide Web in
     1994.

